Abdomen:
somewhat more fusiform; relatively short; convex; urosternites I-IV widest (
0.85 mm
) at middle of III, narrowest (
0.65 mm
) at apex of IV. Urosternite I slightly elongate (
0.95 mm
), sides straight; II and III (
0.60 mm
), II sides almost straight, III sides weakly rounded, IV (
0.50 mm
) sides weakly rounded. Urosternite V (
0.35 mm
) trapezoidal, transverse; sides sharply pointed (and the same when viewed laterally). Abdominal process a large, wide isosceles triangle (with broad apex) coplanar with abdomen. Apical tergite convex.

Legs:
ratio length front/middle/hind leg 1.0:1.1:3.4; and body length/length of leg 2.6, 2.4, 0.8 respectively. Front and middle legs: moderately slender, front leg rather long; their claves somewhat tumid mesally and widest at middle (when viewed from above). Front leg: tibia gradually widening to apex; apico-lateral margin not toothed. Middle leg: femur 1.60 longer than tibia; length of femur/lateral width of clave 4.00. Hind leg: length 
8.25 mm
; clave comparatively long and weakly abrupt; lengths clave/ peduncle 0.49; femora (
3.65 mm
) 1.07 longer than tibiae (
3.40 mm
); tibia bisinuate (when viewed from above), almost straight (when viewed from the side); tarsus short (
1.20 mm
), about one third length of tibia, and narrower than apex of latter; metatarsomere I gradually widened to apex, 1.25 longer than lengths of II+III.

